        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 7:30PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 729 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Keosauqua, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bonaparte, Mt Hamill, Donnellson, Van Buren County Fairgrounds,
Keosauqua, Keosauqua Airport, Lee County Fairgrounds, Mount Zion,
Utica, Houghton, Indian Lake Park, Primrose, Hillsboro, Lake Sugema
Campground, Lacey Keosauqua State Park, Mount Sterling,
Bentonsport/Vernon, Farmington, Cantril, and Salem.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
